    },
    {
      "line": 10,
      "text": "¥2500 Japan"
    },
    {
      "line": 13,
      "text": "George Gilder * Susan Gritfin ¢ Stewart Brand ¢ Howard Rheingold ¢ Brian"
    },
    {
      "line": 16,
      "text": "-Z ~O, emceee"
    },
    {
      "line": 19,
      "text": "NO ABSOLUTES"
    },
    {
      "line": 20,
      "text": "JUST TOOLS"
    },
    {
      "line": 23,
      "text": "SUBSCRIBE TO WHOLE EARTH REVIEW"
    },
    {
      "line": 24,
      "text": "CALL CARLOS AT 415/332-1716 OR FAX 415/332-3110"
    },
    {
      "line": 25,
      "text": "TOLL FREE ORDER LINE: 800/783-4903"
    },
    {
      "line": 28,
      "text": "mes have changed"
    },
    {
      "line": 29,
      "text": "and the world comes to us in different ways."
    },
    {
      "line": 30,
      "text": "as leaped from the page to the screen,"
    },
    {
      "line": 31,
      "text": "ds to be seen as well as heard,"
    },
    {
      "line": 32,
      "text": "compaters have jumbled our relationship to"
    },
    {
      "line": 33,
      "text": "information, surveillance and money,"
    },
    {
      "line": 34,
      "text": "and television has merely changed everything."
    },
    {
      "line": 35,
      "text": "Now, things feel like they’re moving really fast,"
    },
    {
      "line": 36,
      "text": "leaving us with the attention spans of kitties"
    },
    {
      "line": 37,
      "text": "riveted by mouse-like movements."
    },
    {
      "line": 38,
      "text": "Within the blink of a blind eye,"
    },
    {
      "line": 39,
      "text": "we are soaked in sales pitches and infotainments"
    },
    {
      "line": 40,
      "text": "that make history when they do business."
    },
    {
      "line": 43,
      "text": "Running in place at the speed of light,"
    },
    {
      "line": 44,
      "text": "we defensively cling to our unexamined notions of categories,"
    },
    {
      "line": 45,
      "text": "our dilapidated signposts in a bleak landscape."
    },
    {
      "line": 46,
      "text": "They make things simple again."
    },
    {
      "line": 47,
      "text": "Reflections of control,"
    },
    {
      "line": 50,
      "text": "they reassure us that there’s a time and a place for everything."
    },
    {
      "line": 53,
      "text": "Declaring what’s right and what’s wrong,"
    },
    {
      "line": 54,
      "text": "they strengthen stereotypes and"
    },
    {
      "line": 55,
      "text": "murmur the false humilities of “common sense.”"
    },
    {
      "line": 56,
      "text": "Glowing with a veneer of studied connoisseurship,"
    },
    {
      "line": 57,
      "text": "they can grow nostalgic for times that never were."
    },
    {
      "line": 58,
      "text": "They are easy systems."
    },
    {
      "line": 60,
      "text": "Use them, but doubt them."
    },
    {
      "line": 62,
      "text": "They are the rules of the game,"
    },
    {
      "line": 63,
      "text": "but perhaps no longer the one being played."
    },
    {
      "line": 66,
      "text": "-Barbara Kruger"
    }
  ]
}